{"type":"message","id":"ae9bc037","parentId":"a53b4498","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:17:29.500Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse script is still running. Let me wait for it and also read the most recent log file.","thinkingSignature":"a6b3595d0c67e170382195894ce499261cb9c2ba014d51d6ead578f06dd47fec"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_19tis1hw87qq_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"marine-slug","timeout":120000}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_19tis1hw87qq_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 041617.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":404,"output":117,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12475,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774340243870}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f12eecb","parentId":"ae9bc037","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:17:48.898Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_19tis1hw87qq_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4972\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2729\n[file inferred from ACTION] scripts/tic_classifier.ps1\n[mutation proposed] scripts/tic_classifier.ps1\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 041714 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"marine-slug","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4972\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2729\n[file inferred from ACTION] scripts/tic_classifier.ps1\n[mutation proposed] scripts/tic_classifier.ps1\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 041714 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774340268897}}
{"type":"message","id":"f8666b85","parentId":"1f12eecb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:17:48.901Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_19tis1hw87qq_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 041617\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: temporal_invariance_classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, I need to advance the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The pending action is:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe next action should be to implement the TIC classifier. I need to:\r\n\r\n1. First, look at what pulse logs exist in `logs/` directory\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier that:\r\n   - Reads pulse logs\r\n   - Identifies invariant content (things that repeat across pulses)\r\n   - Identifies variant content (things that change)\r\n   - Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me start by examining the logs directory to understand the format of pulse logs.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. List the pulse log files\r\n2. Create a Python script that implements the TIC classifier\r\n3. Run it on the logs\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist first.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier on pulse logs, but I need to first examine the actual pulse log format and structure to build an effective classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine the pulse log directory structure and sample logs to understand the format, then create the TIC classifier implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\n## Purpose\r\nTest hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Approach\r\n1. **Extract invariants**: Content that recurs across multiple pulse logs\r\n2. **Extract variants**: Content that changes between pulses\r\n3. **Classify**: Determine invariant vs variant classification accuracy\r\n4. **Predict**: Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\nTests: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom difflib import SequenceMatcher\r\n\r\ndef extract_log_content(log_path):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key content from a pulse log file.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(log_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract sections\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    \r\n    # Goals section\r\n    goals_match = re.search(r'### Active\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if goals_match:\r\n        sections['goals'] = goals_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    # Pending section\r\n    pending_match = re.search(r'## Pending\\n(.*?)(?=\\n##|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if pending_match:\r\n        sections['pending'] = pending_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    # Observation/Action\r\n    obs_match = re.search(r'### OBSERVATION\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if obs_match:\r\n        sections['observation'] = obs_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    return sections, content\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Simple tokenization.\"\"\"\r\n    return re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n\r\ndef find_invariants(all_content, threshold=0.7):\r\n    \"\"\"Find tokens that appear consistently across logs.\"\"\"\r\n    token_counts = Counter()\r\n    total_logs = len(all_content)\r\n    \r\n    for content in all_content:\r\n        tokens = set(tokenize(content))\r\n        for token in tokens:\r\n            token_counts[token] += 1\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant = appears in >threshold of logs\r\n    invariants = {\r\n        token: count / total_logs \r\n        for token, count in token_counts.items() \r\n        if count / total_logs >= threshold and len(token) > 2\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(content, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify content tokens as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    tokens = tokenize(content)\r\n    invariant_tokens = []\r\n    variant_tokens = []\r\n    \r\n    for token in tokens:\r\n        if token in invariants:\r\n            invariant_tokens.append(token)\r\n        elif len(token) > 2:\r\n            variant_tokens.append(token)\r\n    \r\n    return invariant_tokens, variant_tokens\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(prior_logs, current_log):\r\n    \"\"\"Use invariants from prior logs to predict current log.\"\"\"\r\n    prior_content = ' '.join(prior_logs)\r\n    current_sections, _ = extract_log_content(current_log)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract invariants from prior\r\n    invariants = find_invariants(prior_logs)\r\n    \r\n    # Check prediction accuracy on sections\r\n    predictions = {}\r\n    for section_name, section_content in current_sections.items():\r\n        inv_tokens, var_tokens = classify_content(section_content, invariants)\r\n        predictions[section_name] = {\r\n            'invariant_ratio': len(inv_tokens) / max(len(tokenize(section_content)), 1),\r\n            'invariant_count': len(inv_tokens),\r\n            'variant_count': len(var_tokens)\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n    return predictions\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Run the full TIC experiment.\"\"\"\r\n    logs_dir = Path('logs')\r\n    pulse_logs = sorted(logs_dir.glob('pulse_*.md'))\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_logs) < 3:\r\n        print(f\"Need at least 3 pulse logs, found {len(pulse_logs)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"TIC Experiment: Analyzing {len(pulse_logs)} pulse logs\\n\")\r\n    \r\n    # Extract all content\r\n    all_content = []\r\n    all_sections = []\r\n    for log in pulse_logs:\r\n        sections, content = extract\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:16:49\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774340268898}}
